Sentencas: In the present work, the Ruddlesden-Popper (RP) phases La2NiO4+delta (La2) and La4Ni3O10 +/-delta (La4) were employed as cathode materials with Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta (GDC) electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Impact of electrical conductivity and the electrochemical performance of La2NiO4+δ and La4Ni3O10±δ cathodes on symmetric cells for intermediate-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Cathode inks were deposited on the GDC substrate by the dip-coating technique.
Titulo: Impact of electrical conductivity and the electrochemical performance of La2NiO4+δ and La4Ni3O10±δ cathodes on symmetric cells for intermediate-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The electrochemical properties of the cathode in symmetric cells with GDC were investigated.
Titulo: Impact of electrical conductivity and the electrochemical performance of La2NiO4+δ and La4Ni3O10±δ cathodes on symmetric cells for intermediate-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The area-specific resistance (ASR) of the La4Ni3O10 +/-delta cathode is lower than that of the La2NiO4+delta cathode at 600, 700, and 800 degrees C, with values of 6.91, 1.22, and 0.23 Omega cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Impact of electrical conductivity and the electrochemical performance of La2NiO4+δ and La4Ni3O10±δ cathodes on symmetric cells for intermediate-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: These values are better than other RP families previously reported.
Titulo: Impact of electrical conductivity and the electrochemical performance of La2NiO4+δ and La4Ni3O10±δ cathodes on symmetric cells for intermediate-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: This work combines cathode layers to form multilayers as a La2La4La2 symmetric cell, enhancing the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) properties, which exhibit an ASR value of 0.12 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C. We report a performance in a symmetric cell using a configuration with La2 and La4 cathodes that could be a promising alternative for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Impact of electrical conductivity and the electrochemical performance of La2NiO4+δ and La4Ni3O10±δ cathodes on symmetric cells for intermediate-temperature SOFCs
